The techno-organic raised himself from the chair of the computer operator. 
He felt a bit dizzy from the download, but not too much.

Gesper:
Here, this should work now. Computer, spark scan in a radius of 300 miles 
from here.

The holoscreen projected a detailed map of the region and showed three 
sparks at the center.

Belthassan:
(with a smile) I knew I could count on you!

Melchana entered the room, her training session obviously having helped to 
manage her fury.

Melchana:
Okay, I found the problem about the diversion core. I'll skip 
technicalities, the main thing is that it's out of order for a while. We'll 
have to replace it entirely. If the shield are online, though, they'd still 
be able to prevent damages.

Belthassan:
Great job, both of you! Now, I'll contact Zardus and try to make a deal with 
him. Computer, open a frequency with the Alliance.
This message is destined to Zardus of the Alliance. I am Belthassan, leader 
of the Prophets and Tripredacus officer in command of the Earth stage of 
operation. As you have met my friend and colleague Daemos, I suggest that 
our two factions ally. I think we have many points in common and that we 
could provide many benefits to each other.
